	<h2>Hearing Test: Where It All Begins</h2>
	<p>
		A hearing test at Commonwealth Audiology is the first step toward
		understanding your hearing health. We begin with a gentle ear exam followed
		by a series of precise, comfortable tests that give us a complete picture
		of how you're hearing.
	</p>
	<p>
		Your evaluation always includes pure-tone audiometry, which measures your
		ability to hear different pitches and frequencies, and speech testing,
		which assesses how clearly you understand spoken words. In most cases, we
		also include speech-in-noise testing to better reflect real-world listening
		situations. Depending on your hearing history and communication needs,
		additional testing may be recommended to ensure we fully understand your
		hearing health.
	</p>
	<p>
		Together, these assessments help us determine the exact type and degree of
		hearing loss, if present. By establishing your individual hearing
		thresholds, we gain the detailed information needed to recommend the most
		appropriate hearing solution for your needs. This step is essential in
		making sure any recommendation is tailored specifically to your hearing
		profile and supports your day-to-day communication needs and quality of
		life.
	</p>
	<p>
		Once we review your results, we'll walk through everything in clear, simple
		terms and discuss a care plan that fits your lifestyle and goals.
		Throughout the entire process, Dr. Tiffany Brewer provides expert guidance
		with clarity, compassion, and support, every step of the way.
	</p>

